    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>KOREA TO SELL STEEL STAKE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Samuel Len</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>State-run Korea Development Bank to sell its remaining 9.8 percent stake in the Pohang Iron and Steel Co (Posco) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The South Korean government will sell its remaining 9.8 percent stake in the Pohang Iron and Steel Company, or Posco. The state-run Korea Development Bank will sell a 6.8 percent stake in the steel giant in the United States, Europe and Asia by issuing depository receipts. The remaining 3 percent will go to domestic investors. About one-third of Posco's shares are already held by foreigners.</p>
        <p>Samuel Len</p>
      </block>
